(* Source files for sml-jwt, in dependency order.

   The vendored sml-crypto sources are pulled in first; that include *itself*
   pulls in the vendored sml-codec sources (SHA-256 for HMAC + Base64 for the
   base64url adapter), so sml-codec is included exactly once even though we use
   it directly. sml-json (and its own vendored sml-parsec) come next, then our
   own files. Listing sml-codec separately here would double-include it and
   error, so we deliberately rely on the transitive include from sml-crypto. *)

$(SML_LIB)/basis/basis.mlb

../sml-crypto/sources.mlb
../sml-json/sources.mlb

jwt.sig
jwt.sml
